OL,4,CAlmost 7,000 waiting for lifesaving
OL,5,Ctransplants
OL,6, Almost 7,000 people are waiting for
OL,7, lifesaving transplants in the UK - the
OL,8, highest number in six years, estimates
OL,9, by NHS Blood and Transplant show.
OL,11,FThe analysis, from April 2020 to March
OL,12,F2021, found some key services closed
OL,13,Fduring the first peak of the pandemic.
OL,15,FBut many were rapidly reinstated and
OL,16,Foverall 80% of NHS transplant work did
OL,17,Ftake place, researchers say.
OL,19,FThe figures show 3,391 people were
OL,20,Fgiven transplants over the year, with
OL,21,Fmore than 1,180 donating organs.
